  "title": "Research Fellow (High-Performance AI Computing Systems)",
  "description": "<p>Interested applicants are invited to apply directly at the <a href=\"https://careers.nus.edu.sg/job/Research-Fellow-%28High-Performance-AI-Computing-Systems%29/31506-en_GB/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>NUS\nCareer Portal</strong></a></p><p>Your application will be processed only if you apply\nvia <a href=\"https://careers.nus.edu.sg/job/Research-Fellow-%28High-Performance-AI-Computing-Systems%29/31506-en_GB/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>NUS\nCareer Portal</strong></a></p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.<br /></p><h2><strong>Job Description</strong></h2><p>We are seeking a highly motivated and skilled Research Fellow to join our team on a project to demonstrate high-performance AI computing systems. The successful candidate will be part of an interdisciplinary research team working on the design, fabrication, and integration of neuromorphic computing architectures targeted at next-generation AI workloads. </p><p>Key Responsibilities:<br />•    Conduct cutting-edge research in AI computing architectures, including neural networks hardware accelerator systems.<br />•    Design, model, and simulate memristor cells and circuits tailored for AI acceleration.<br />•    Collaborate on the fabrication and experimental characterization of integrated memristor devices and systems.<br />•    Develop algorithms and system-level integration strategies to harness the capabilities of AI accelerator for machine learning and deep learning tasks.<br />•    Publish research findings in high-impact journals and present at international conferences.<br />•    Mentor graduate and undergraduate students involved in the project.</p><h2><strong>Qualifications</strong></h2><p>•    PhD in Electrical Engineering, Materials Science, Applied Physics, or a related field.<br />•    Experience in device modeling and simulation.<br />•    Prior hands-on experience with cleanroom fabrication and optical/electrical characterization is an advantage.<br />•    Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.<br />•    Ability to work independently and in a collaborative team environment.<br />•    Excellent publication record in reputable peer-reviewed journals.</p>",
